<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title></title>
        <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
        <link href="css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
        <link href="css/uniform.default.min.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
        <link href="css/custom.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
    </head>

    <body>
        <header>
            <div class="container-fluid mid_grey" id="header-container">
              <h1>sachet</h1>
              <h2>Handcraft your development environment</h2>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="container-fluid" id="main-container">
            <div class="row-fluid" id="main-container-row">
                <div class="span5 description">
                  <p class="lead welcome">
                    <i class="icon-magic icon-large"></i> Welcome to sachet
                  </p>

                  <p class="lead part1">
                    <i class="icon-magic icon-large"></i> Customize &rarr; General
                  </p>

                  <p class="lead part2">
                    <i class="icon-magic icon-large"></i> Customize &rarr; Theme
                  </p>

                  <p class="lead part3">
                    <i class="icon-magic icon-large"></i> Customize &rarr; Plugins
                  </p>

                  <p class="welcome">
                    sachet allows you to handcraft your VIM development environment. 
                    By allowing you to select features and functionality that <b>you</b>
                    are comfortable with, sachet generates you a small package with 
                    the appropriate configuration files, plugins, and theme so you can
                    leverage the potential of your VIM editor.
                    <hr />
                  </p>

                  <p class="part1">Select the built-in options that you would like to enable.</p>

                  <p class="part2">
                    Select the theme that you would like to use.
                    <br /><br />
                    Note: Some themes require a 256-color terminal to be used. If you are 
                    using Mac, <a href="http://www.iterm2.com/#/section/home" target="_blank">
                      iTerm</a> is a great terminal
                    that will suit your needs. For any other *nix distribution, read 
                    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/256_colors_in_vim" target="_blank">
                      this article</a> on how to enable 256-color support.
                  </p>

                  <p class="part3">Select the plugins that you would like to use.</p>

                </div>

                <div class="display">
                  <div class="span7">
                    <div id="part1">
                      <%= erb :configuration, :locals => {:configuration => configuration} %>
                    </div>

                    <% [themes, plugins].each do |content| %>
                      <% group = (content == themes) ? 'part2' : 'part3' %>

                      <div id="<%= group %>">
                        <%= erb :gallery, :locals => {:group => group, :content => content} %>
                      </div>
                    <% end %>

                    <a class="btn btn-primary" id="previous_btn">Previous</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-primary" id="next_btn">Next</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <script src="js/jquery.js"></script>
        <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
        <script src="js/jquery.uniform.js"></script>
        <script src="js/custom.js"></script>
    </body>
</html>
